com.google.enterprise.adaptor.testing

Class UnsupportedRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.enterprise.adaptor.testing.UnsupportedRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Request

    public class UnsupportedRequest
extends Object
implements Request
    An implementation of Request that throws an UnsupportedOperationException if any method is called.

    This class is intended to be extended for unit testing, rather than implementing the Request interface directly.

    See Also:
    DocRequest

      • hasChangedSinceLastAccess

        public boolean hasChangedSinceLastAccess(Date lastModified)
        Description copied from interface: Request
        Returns true if the GSA or other client's current copy of the document was retrieved after the lastModified date; false otherwise. lastModified must be in GMT.

        If false, the client does not need to be re-sent the data, since what they have cached is the most recent version. In this case, you should then call Response.respondNotModified().

        Specified by:

        whether updated content should be sent

      • canRespondWithNoContent

        public boolean canRespondWithNoContent(Date lastModified)
        Description copied from interface: Request
        Returns true if the GSA or other client's current copy of the document was retrieved after the lastModified date and GSA can handle HTTP 204 response; false otherwise. lastModified must be in GMT.

        If true, the client does not need to be re-sent the file content , since what they have cached is the most recent version. In this case, you should then call Response.respondNoContent().

      • getLastAccessTime

        public Date getLastAccessTime()
        Description copied from interface: Request
        Returns the last time a GSA or other client retrieved the data, or null if none was provided by the client. The returned Date is in GMT.

        This is useful for determining if the client needs to be re-sent the data since what they have cached may be the most recent version. If the client is up-to-date, then call Response.respondNotModified().

        Specified by:
        getLastAccessTime in interface Request
        Returns:

        UnsupportedOperationException - always

        Provides the document ID for the document that is being requested. DocId was not necessarily provided previously by the Adaptor; it is client-provided and must not be trusted.
